cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.MM, cs.DS, cs.NI. 

The paper deals with information theory and communication systems, specifically focusing on encoding schemes for degraded broadcast channels. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the properties of the conditional entropy bound function and applies it to achieve capacity, which falls under the scope of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also introduces permutation encoding, which is related to cs.MM (Multimedia), and provides explicit parametric expressions, which is related to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture).
